iously unsolvable problems, and dream up solutions we didn=E2=80=99t even k=
now we needed.=C2=A0
All to say, there=E2=80=99s reason to be optimistic. I=E2=80=99ve spent the=
 last year plus at Not Boring trying to lay out the rational case for optim=
ism, for why, regardless of short-term volatility, things will continue to =
trend up from here [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEluhDAQRU_T3gV5pP=
HCi2xyDctDAVaDjYwdRJ8-DkiJVINUpaqv_5wpMKV8qi3tBf0WXc4NVIRjX6AUyKjukHXwivR0Y=
IJL5BX3ZBADCrseM8BqwqJKroC2apfgTAkpXhcYU4FmJaT1gx8HYP3IrcSSSkGGfhxtj11v8K1r=
qg8QHSj4hnymCGhRcynb_mCfD_rV4jiOLqZiUw5x6lxqo62lS-uWavRt-OGyeZ8oKIopIZQwwkT=
PcUe7p2GCEQPSctlL7LqTvOfMX_OD43Wi3V7tXox7tbcryupPpq1fs1lhuRbNoG59rTGUU0M0dg=
F_ey83wouGniBCbmi9NqWBY5JjNhDMibi9NjhcsCdjjU9T9qldxX_RH4EziVw]. Optimism ha=
s been the financially dominant strategy for at least the past two decades,=
 and I want us to sound smart, too:=C2=A0
Now, =E2=80=9Cbe more optimistic=E2=80=9D isn=E2=80=99t particularly action=
able advice on which to end the year. Being optimistic shouldn=E2=80=99t ju=
st mean sitting passively by and waiting for good things to happen. But how=
 do you orient and act in a world that=E2=80=99s moving and evolving so qui=
ckly?=C2=A0
I=E2=80=99ve written about Worldbuilders [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/=
eJxFkMtqhTAQQL_mZqfk5WuRRTf9DYnJqOFqIsmkYr--qUIL84AZhsMcoxGWEC91hITkt4x4HaA=
8nGkDRIgkJ4ijs4q1vBeNHIhV0rK-6YlL4xwBdu02hTEDOfK0OaPRBX9fUMobsqpukrZvxWQ7bm=
G2cyuG3hrNJJO6BQ0PV2frwBtQ8AXxCh7IplbEI73Ex4t_ljjPs_YBpxCdX2oTyugoiWeoTn2lC=
kN1RLDOYIUrVHPGHIE4xSlnjDPBRNNKWvO606IRTMMwyaEdqKkv9r1G-V5fku4Lr1OeEmrzLoyd=
RPXHLOv3qnfY7kX5dix9z97hNYLX0wb2EYGPz1vNuICHWDzbUWOxKAZJRc-oZM3zeDElG9EJUWQ=
Vsg3lyv9DfwCtto69] a lot here =E2=80=93 people who predict something non-ob=
vious about the way the world is moving, create a seemingly small wedge int=
o a much larger opportunity, timestamp their vision, and then execute patie=
ntly but aggressively to make it a reality. The worldbuilders we=E2=80=99ve=
 covered are people like Elon Musk, Jeff Bezos, and the founders of unicorn=
 startups, but I think the same thing works for regular people like us.=C2=
=A0
Formulate a decade-long view of where everything is heading, where you want=
 it to head, and what role you=E2=80=99re best-suited to play in making tha=
t happen.=C2=A0
This past year was a blast. People jumped from project to project, from min=
t to mint, from DAO to DAO. It was a year during which experimentation was =
the purpose. It was a lot of fun.=C2=A0
But, at least for me, it also meant that there was less time to think longe=
r-term and to get more deeply involved in a few projects working towards th=
ings that will take more than a few weeks to play out. As things move faste=
r and faster, it=E2=80=99s more and more important to hit pause, evaluate, =
and plan.=C2=A0
Personally, I=E2=80=99m going to read a lot, write thoughts not meant for p=
ublic consumption, put some systems in place, and try to anchor myself to a=
 longer-term vision of where the world is heading and how I can best contri=
bute.=C2=A0
That will be a loose guide. When the madness starts back up in January, I=
=E2=80=99ll try to act like a Bayesian [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJ=
xFkEmOxCAMRU9TLBFjhgWLrkVfAzE4CUoCEZAupU_fVGXRkmXLtuyv_5ypMKd8qSOVit5J1-sAF=
eFVNqgVMjoLZB28oh0buBQj8kp4OsgBhaKnDLCbsKmaT0DHabfgTA0pfi4IYRItyrLekUFMxE9O=
DKaz4CidRgId8T1z_NY1pw8QHSj4gXylCGhTS61HefCvB_tuARG_whoO8MHglOc2evetPM0FJZi=
mGifI7y8oKEYYpYxyymUnCGa4N1xyamC0YuxG4vBFf5cs1uUhyD4zXE5bqnErdmlHWcVUbcohzm=
29LmaH7bNoJnWr-xlDvTREYzfwt_96Y_wQ0TNEyA2v16Y2eHwUhA-UCCpvvw2QkLznvDFqyj61q=
_gv-gfpa4rs], tethered to my priors but updating my understanding and appro=
ach as I receive new information. That=E2=80=99s why I=E2=80=99m not making=
 any annual predictions: a year is both too short and too long a time frame=
 for me to have conviction.=C2=A0
So I=E2=80=99m not setting anything in stone, but I think that having a lon=
ger-term view will help me pick and choose among the myriad paths that spri=
ng up every day. I=E2=80=99ll probably say =E2=80=9Cyes=E2=80=9D to fewer t=
hings next year, but go in more deeply on those yeses.=C2=A0
Each of your approaches will be totally different. Many of you are probably=
 already working towards that thing you want to come true in a decade; mayb=
e you need a little more experimentation to keep yourself fresh. Others kno=
w that you=E2=80=99re not doing what you want to be doing; it=E2=80=99s pro=
bably time to evaluate, adjust, and start taking steps towards changing tha=
t. Some, like me, are doing too many things and might benefit from a more s=
table north star.=C2=A0=C2=A0
Whatever you do, approach all of the novelty out there with an open mind. Y=
ou can be skeptical, of course, but be curiously skeptical. Don=E2=80=99t d=
efault to cynicism, and don=E2=80=99t dismiss new things out of hand.=C2=A0
New things will seem weird at first, and then those weird things will seem =
normal, and other, newer things will seem weird, and on and on.=C2=A0
At some point =E2=80=93 it might be March 2022, December 2029, or April 206=
9 =E2=80=93 everything that we=E2=80=99ve created and experienced in 2021 w=
ill seem quaint and antiquated. If we=E2=80=99re lucky, today=E2=80=99s mos=
t out-there ideas and technologies will be tiny building blocks in much lar=
ger structures.=C2=A0
Of course there will be failures along the way. If there aren=E2=80=99t, we=
=E2=80=99re not dreaming big enough. You can choose to point to each stumbl=
e and yell, =E2=80=9CI told you so!=E2=80=9D or you can choose to zoom out,=
 applaud the experimentation, and chip in where you can to make the next on=
e better.=C2=A0
You know which one I=E2=80=99m choosing. I have no idea what the next year =
will bring, but I know that on a long enough time horizon, we=E2=80=99re go=
ing to keep pushing out the Pareto Funtier [https://email.mg2.substack.com/=
c/eJxFkN1uhCAQhZ9muVvDr6sXXPSmr2FGmFWyCgbGGvv0pWvSJsAknMycOZ8Dwinl026pEPt9B=
jo3tBGPsiARZrYXzEPwVrSyU0b3zFvtRWc6FsrwzIgrhMVS3pFt-7gEBxRSfHdwLg2bLXA9Qt8K=
AZ0ejTNaCe9BGuEkqA755Qu7DxgdWvzCfKaIbLEz0VZu6uMmP-s5jqOJicaUQ5wal-rXVi_NeN8=
gI6X7c48U6s7BSi6FkEIJZVrNG9k8QBklAPtR923PXXOK7znr13zTfJ1kU_axELhXnbuybP98qv=
yaYcXlLdSEQ63rHgOdA0YYF_RXeLoYvnEME0bMla0fgCo51WuuOsG1MFfYSkcb9VCqAqrOPtWu-=
G_6A6ryiVM], fix the planet, and make life better for as many of the eight =
billion of us as possible. That=E2=80=99s what humans do.=C2=A0
The best is still yet to come.
